--- Definitions ---

login shell 	- prompted for username/password (SSH, su -)
non-login shell - terminal session started from GUI (when you start shell from existing session)

--- Startup files (login shell) ---

/etc/profile		# Global config for all users
~/.bash_profile 	# User's personal startup file. Can override global startup file
~/.bash_login		# Used if .bash_profle not present
~/.profile		# Used if neither .bash_profile nor .bash_login present

--- Startup files (non-login shell) ---

~/.bashrc		# Used specifically for interactive, non-login shells
/etc/bash.bashrc	# Global config for all users
/etc/.bashrc		# User's personal startup file
